			<div class="div-comment" id="div-comment-615658">
				<div class="comment-meta clearfix">
					<div class="comment-author-avatar">
						<a class="avatar-placeholder" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da3ae54ddffe5520efe65681766d19d8?d=retro&amp;s=55&amp;r=pg"></a>					</div>
					<div class="comment-info">
						<cite>TT</cite>
						<a href="http://gigaom.com/2011/04/08/10-things-you-never-knew-you-could-do-on-your-ipad/#comment-615658" class="comment-permalink">Saturday, April 9 2011</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="comment-content">
					<div class="comment-text">
						<p>There are 4-finger gestures to bring up the app tray and change between apps, and there is one 5-finger gesture to go back to the home screen (pinch with 5 fingers). They seem to work perfectly fine for me and I just love them. Recently tried out the iPad2 in a store and got annoyed pretty fast by the missing gestures. I hope they get official soon.</p>
